    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-21T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-21T04:00:00-05:00" n="1190"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1190">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.13/9–2154: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Vietnam</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Heath</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Saigon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-21T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 21, 1954—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1143. Repeated information Paris 390. As Embassy had received report (<gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 1125 repeated Paris 386)<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d1190fn1">
                        <ref target="#d1189">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> General <persName corresp="#p_NVH1">Hinh</persName> preparing
                        <hi rend="italic">coup de force</hi> for today, Counselor <persName
                        corresp="#p_KRA1">Kidder</persName> was instructed call on <persName
                        corresp="#p_NVH1">Hinh</persName> in company General <persName
                        corresp="#p_ODLGJW1">O’Daniel</persName> last night to make crystal clear
                    fact that any use force against legal government would necessitate review of
                    entire US policy towards remaining Vietnam. Point emphasized US desires do
                    everything possible support remaining Vietnam, but only on condition country
                    unified in face common danger.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NVH1">Hinh</persName> protested strongly he had no
                    intention use force either on his own behalf or on behalf anyone else against
                    government. He reiterated he has no personal political ambition, that more than
                    anything else he would be delighted if he could retire and go to Beaux Arts in
                    Paris. However, he said his retiring would serve no useful purpose for country
                    as present situation with inefficient government which must be replaced would be
                    unchanged.</p>
                <p>Balance of conversation was carried by General <persName corresp="#p_ODLGJW1"
                        >O’Daniel</persName> who once again attempted persuade <persName
                        corresp="#p_NVH1">Hinh</persName> that he should follow role proper to
                    military and leave matters relating to civilian government to civilians.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NVH1">Hinh</persName>’s view on this that situation so
                    serious and pressure of army on him so strong that it too late. Nevertheless in
                    reply to query re what type of government he would visualize to replace
                        <persName corresp="#p_NDD1">Diem</persName>, he stated evasively he a
                    military man and that not his province.</p>
                <p>Reply from <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao Dai</persName> to <persName
                        corresp="#p_NVH1">Hinh</persName>’s telegram (see <gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 1107 repeated Paris 378)<note n="2" xml:id="d1190fn2">See
                            <ref target="#d1187fn1">footnote 1, p. 2037</ref>.</note> broadcast over
                    local radio this morning is limited to innocuous statement appreciation
                        <persName corresp="#p_NVH1">Hinh</persName>’s expression esteem for His
                    Majesty’s intention, in interest of National Army, look into problem posed by
                        <persName corresp="#p_NVH1">Hinh</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_BD1">Bao
                        Dai</persName>’s message cannot be considered in any sense rebuke of
                        <persName corresp="#p_NVH1">Hinh</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Heath</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
